programme.desc: 56-year-old Michael is living every parent's worst nightmare. His six-year-old son Dylan has been missing for three months now. His ex-wife didn't return him after a routine weekend visit and now he fears that she's trying to smuggle him out of Bali.

programme.title: Danger Beach: Episode 1
programme.desc: Muriwai lifeguard's first rescue of the season is of an unexpected nature and on a remote part of the beach. Lifeguards rush to the aid of a distraught 18-year-old girl whose been sucked into a treacherous hole.

programme.title: Danger Beach: Episode 2
programme.desc: Lifeguards struggle to keep swimmers safe as swift rips sweep them out of the flagged area. But for one boogie boarder it's too late. The young guns are put to the test as a surfer is pounded by huge swells and dragged across jagged rocks.

programme.title: Danger Beach: Episode 3
programme.desc: It's looking like another perfect day for the mounting crowd at Muriwai Beach, but lifeguards soon have a crisis on their hands as a full scale search is mounted for a young boy.

programme.title: Danger Beach: Episode 4
programme.desc: A surfer washes up on Muriwai Beach and lifeguards are unsure what's wrong with him. Lifeguards could be forced to shut the beach because of an invasion of a swarm of jellyfish.

programme.title: Danger Beach: Episode 5
programme.desc: With the summer season in full swing the veteran guards decide to teach the Rookie's some new tricks. A shark sighting has the entire beach on full alert. And the relentless rips prove too much for one Canadian tourist.

programme.title: Danger Beach: Episode 6
programme.desc: Inviting surf conditions cause chaos's as the mix of boards and swimmers ends in tears. Could engine failure be disastrous for Muriwai lifeguards as a group of inexperience surfers are swept out to sea. And the pounding surf shows the IRB crew whose boss.

programme.title: Danger Beach: Episode 7
programme.desc: Record crowds leave lifeguards frustrated as veteran Garth McCullough's worst fear comes true. Training turns real as young rookie Mackenzie makes her first rescue.

programme.title: Danger Beach: Episode 8
programme.desc: Muriwai reputations are put on the line as they battle for supremacy at the State National Championship. It's back to work for Doctor Slim as the sand dunes bite back. And the young guns step up to keep Danger Beach safe.

programme.title: Danger Beach: Episode 9
programme.desc: Huge swells and king tides cause torment for the Muriwai lifeguards. A surfer gets sliced and sucked out to sea. A standup paddle boarders goes missing around the treacherous Flat Rock. And an IRB training exercise goes horribly wrong at Danger Beach.

programme.title: Danger Beach: Episode 10
programme.desc: It's business as usual for lifeguards on the final patrol of the summer and the stormy weather is making Muriwai look like a scene out of Gothic Beach. Flat Rock causes bloodshed as a rookie guard takes on the elements.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 6
programme.desc: Retirees Diane and husband Gary were just a few hours into their Pacific Island cruise of a lifetime when disaster struck. Diane toppled down a set of stairs and now she's in need of urgent medical attention.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 5
programme.desc: A truck driver who had one leg amputated 40 years ago, has crashed his truck and crushed his remaining leg. If Rescue 1 can't get him to hospital in time, he will bleed to death.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 6
programme.desc: Westpac chopper paramedic Bruce Kerr has a frantic battle to save a car crash victim with a life-threatening head injury.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 7
programme.desc: Auckland's Westpac helicopter crew races to save a 39 year old forestry worker who has been struck on the head leaving him paralyzed from the waist down.

programme.title: Chopper Squad: Episode 8
programme.desc: The chopper crew races to save a woman with a rare disease who's in danger of suffocating from uncontrollable muscle spasms; a badly burnt toddler at Cooks Beach needs an urgent airlift to hospital.

programme.title: Motorvision Special: Ice Action Finland
programme.desc: Former World Rally Champion Armin Schwarz is a legend behind the wheels. Now he is instructing other talented people in driving a 300 hp Subaru WRX STI rally car on the snowy and icy, but also breathtaking landscape of Finland.

programme.title: Motorvision Special: Racechip Challenge
programme.desc: More power and yet better fuel economy? With chip tuning this is supposed to be possible. We want to check this out and send two teams on a road trip with a difference. From Uhingen near Stuttgart in Germany, we travel to Barcelona and back.

programme.title: Motorvision Special: New Car Purchase Experience

programme.title: Motorvision Special: 90 Years BMW Motor Bike

programme.title: Motorvision Special: The Car of the Future
programme.desc: The car of the future - this is how it might look: Aerodynamic, light and quiet. And with almost no fuel consumption. This is how we could soon travel on roads. But is a car like this just a pipe dream of engineers?

programme.title: Motorvision Special: Isle of Mann TT 2015 Documentary

programme.title: Motorvision Special: Vintage Airplane Show Days

programme.title: Motorvision Special: Germany´s Supercar Rally

programme.title: On Tour: Night of the Jumps

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: Body in the Freezer
programme.desc: A meeting between two businessmen leaves one shot in the face. Things seem cut and dry until Lt. Kenda realizes the “victim” could actually be the aggressor, shot struggling over his own gun.

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: Death Rains Down
programme.desc: Restaurant worker Sharon Coleman is murdered in a hail of large caliber gunfire. Kenda must break through a web of lies to hunt down one of the most dangerous criminal masterminds he’s ever faced.

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: Blood Red Highway
programme.desc: The elderly owners of a local grocery are attacked and left for dead. Working with a vague witness description, Lt. Joe Kenda leads a state-wide manhunt to catch a pair of cold-blooded killers.

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: Fate Worst Than Death
programme.desc: At the bottom of a steep ravine, joggers discover a body mutilated beyond recognition. To catch a ruthless maniac, Lt. Joe Kenda must first solve the puzzle of the victim’s identity.

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: The Master Key
programme.desc: When a pregnant mother and her two young sons are brutally slain, pressure mounts for the CSPD to catch the cold-blooded monster who did it.

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: Weapon of Choice
programme.desc: When mother of two Shaundra Murr is run over in front of her house, officers initially suspect a hit and run. Until Lt. Joe Kenda uncovers evidence proving Shaundra’s murder was a crime of passion.

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: River of Blood
programme.desc: Two hunters discover a blood-drenched car, its owner riddled with buckshot. Lt. Joe Kenda learns the car was reported stolen the day before, he follows its trail to a group of unlikely suspects.

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: Eyes Wide Shut
programme.desc: A park ranger discovers the corpse of amateur boxer Corey Edge floating in a shallow creek. Kenda learns the victim had ties to the criminal underworld, and investigates a rogue’s gallery of hustlers.

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Cotton, Ricky, and Lila & Duke

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Fear of Dogs
programme.desc: After being attacked by a dog as a boy, a man must learn to overcome his fear of dogs for the sake of his career and his wife and children. Cesar is called in to exorcise Ernesto’s fear.

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Buddy: Red Alert
programme.desc: Pit Bull Buddy, was found chained and starving to death and was very aggressive. Rufus, a Rottweiler/Shar Pei mix, has bitten five people. Both need to get their aggression under control.

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Tillie and Leo
programme.desc: A rehabilitated Wheaten Terrier mix grows overly attached to his rescuer. The owners of a Shar-pei must deal with the result of their dog’s growing aggression towards other dogs.

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Bodhi, Maggie & Molly, and Bojo
programme.desc: Bloodhound/Catahoula mix, Bojo, is aggressive when it comes to mealtime. Molly and Maggie, two territorial Maltese, and a Kerry Blue Terrier in need of some calm assertive energy.

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Cesar Conquers London
